<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>When
we have a legal term, we must define it.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:Arial'>At common law, all crimes require proof that the conduct
included a voluntary act.<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>� </span>A voluntary
act is defined as �a willed muscular contraction�.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>Are
there any facts in this case that would support a claim by Frank that the
