<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>At
common law, the felony-murder rule is a <i>pure, absolute rule</i>.<span
style='mso-spacerun:yes'>� </span>Any killing that occurs during the attempted
commission of a felony would trigger this rule.<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>�
</span>However, this rule is controversial, and so courts have tried to find
