<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p><b><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>Why
this wasn�t realistic<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p><b><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></b></p>

<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>The
timing was phony.<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>� </span>Everything would take
a lot longer in real life.<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>� </span>Also, the
lawyers would have been involved in jury selection.<span
style='mso-spacerun:yes'>� </span>We didn�t see the witnesses and we missed out
on a lot of other relevant evidence.<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>�
</span>Rusk wouldn�t have had to testify.<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>�
</span>In 95% of criminal cases, the defendant <i>does not</i> testify, even
when the defendant is factually innocent or the attorney <i>thinks</i> the
