</span></span></span><![endif]><span dir=LTR><span style='font-size:14.0pt;
mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>The statute does not use the word �consent� or the
phrase �without consent�.<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>� </span>Instead, the
statute uses the word �coercion�.<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>� </span>Why
might the statute use the word �coercion� rather than the phrase �without
consent�?<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>� </span>The feminist critique was that
too much time was being spent putting the woman on trial, and that instead the
defendant should be put on trial.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l21 level1 lfo28;
