threat.<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>� </span>Under the reasonable belief
requirement, even though the person couldn�t have killed the defendant, the
defendant still is acquitted even though what he did was objectively wrong.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>What
if it turns out that the gun was a toy gun and it was obvious to pretty much
any normal person that the gun wasn�t real?<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>�
</span>Then the defendant loses the self-defense claim because the belief wasn�t
