<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>LaFave
and Scott might have argued that duress requires a threat of <i>death</i> and
it can�t be used as a defense to <i>murder</i>.<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>�
</span>Therefore, they would argue, that death is worse than any conduct that
